Hadoop in layman's term is defined as the splitting a job across dozens or hundreds of computers 
so they can share the load and get the job done faster.


2).components of hadoop framework are listed as:-
a)HDFS-It stands for hadoop distributed file system which stores diffents kinds of data.
b).Map reduce- This is used for processing the data.
c). YARN – It is the resource management framework used for scheduling and handling resource requests from distributed applications.



3).Reasons to learn big data technologies are:-
a).Use of enormous data from mails,mobile,applications,media etc. has mandated the professionals to process bigdata and store the data.
b).Trending job demand with highest package.
c)skill development.
